<section class="hero">
  <h1>Eleven for business</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Chat for small businesses that don't want their plans on someone else's
    servers. End-to-end encrypted, one flat price, and yours to take
    in-house whenever you like.
  </p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#get">Get Eleven</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://home.elevenmessenger.com">Create your space</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-group" aria-label="Why businesses pick Eleven">
  <ul class="cards">
    <li>
      <h3>Your plans stay private</h3>
      <p>
        Supplier prices, payroll, the next move: encrypted on your devices,
        unreadable to us and to anyone who breaks in.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Flat price, not per seat</h3>
      <p>
        One price covers the team. Hiring someone doesn't change your
        invoice.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Clients join with a link</h3>
      <p>
        No seat provisioning, no guest-account dance. Send a link; remove
        them when the job wraps.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Take it in-house any time</h3>
      <p>
        One small program on your own server, same apps, same features.
        <a href="/self-host/">Self-hosting is first class.</a>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Helpers for the boring bits</h3>
      <p>
        Scheduled reminders, morning summaries, little internal tools built
        by asking the built-in helper.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>DMs the boss can't read</h3>
      <p>
        Direct messages are truly end-to-end encrypted: only the two people
        in them hold the keys. Not the admin, not the owner, not us. Your
        team can speak freely — it's a guarantee, not a policy.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>GDPR without the headache</h3>
      <p>
        Members hand us no personal data to process: no emails, no phone
        numbers, no analytics — and messages are encrypted before they
        reach any server. The one record we hold is your billing email;
        if you're paying us, we need to know who you are. The
        <a href="/security/">security model is documented and checkable</a>.
        Strict data residency? <a href="/self-host/">Self-host</a> and
        nothing leaves your building.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Fast on everything</h3>
      <p>
        The whole app is smaller than a photo. The warehouse Android and
        the old front-desk laptop run it fine.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    <a href="/features/">All the features &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</section>

